<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 29 at 1:17AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT OVERNIGHT...
WEATHER...
* Light to moderate snow continues across the area early this
morning with a peak in intensity from now until around 430 AM.
Snowfall rates of around 0.25 to 0.50 inches per hour are
expected. Lighter snow will then continue into the mid-morning
hours.
* Additional snow accumulations of 1 to 2 inches are expected
from 115 AM to 430 AM.
IMPACTS...
* Light snow accumulates more easily on roads at night resulting
in at least short stretches of hazards driving conditions,
particularly on bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the variable
driving conditions by reducing speed and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
